# to host a static website in s3
# the policy is here as follows:-
{
    "Version": "2012-10-17",
    "Statement": [
        {
            "Sid": "PublicReadGetObject",
            "Effect": "Allow",
            "Principal": "*",
            "Action": "s3:GetObject",
            "Resource": "arn:aws:s3:::YOUR_BUCKET_NAME/*"
        }
    ]
}

# block public access (off)
# allow static website hosting

# bucket abac :- to divides the bucket on the basis of tags
# example:- if u have 3 projects and u want to divide the bucket on the basis of projects
# then u can use abac to divide the bucket on the basis of tags

# ============================= cloudfront setup for s3 bucket ==========================
# 1. create a s3 bucket and upload the files
# 2. create a cloudfront distribution
# 3. in origin domain name, select the s3 bucket
# 4. in default cache behavior settings, set viewer protocol policy to redirect http to https
# 5. in distribution settings, set price class to use only selected edge locations
# 6. create the distribution
# 7. after the distribution is deployed, copy the domain name
# 8. access the s3 bucket files using the cloudfront domain name
# 9. to invalidate the cache, go to the invalidations tab and create a new invalidation
# 10. enter /* to invalidate all files
# 11. create the invalidation
# 12. after the invalidation is completed, access the s3 bucket files using the cloudfront domain name again

